==Onepager: User==
Users in the wiki can take four different roles/working fields:
; '''Reader'''
: = browsing through the wiki via dashboards and links to learn more, searching the wiki for specific information
: Browsing through the wiki or searching for specific information, the reader needs clear information architecture, easily accessible dashboards for often used content and a high-performance search with relevant search results.
; '''Contributor/Editor'''
: = contributing with content to the wiki
: The contributor is editing wiki pages on smaller or larger scale: Correcting errors, adding small chunks of information here and there, adding formatting, adding paragraphs of information, adding entirely new pages with a form. She/He is mostly in her/his own field/department/knowledge domain. Editing shall be easy and encouraged.
: She/He uses VE and forms to add/edit text.
; '''Power user/Peers'''
: = dedicated heavy user, technically oriented
: The power user is an active contributor to the wiki and technically oriented. Her/his is interested in the wiki functionalities under the hood and usually has a better grasp of the technical features and formatting options than other users. She/he can be a peer for other users and helps promoting the wiki. Power users are an important driver for the wiki.
: She/He uses also source text to add/change text.
;'''Gardener'''
: The gardener (a dedicated role for power users) helps organizing and structuring the wiki: Categorizing, moving, renaming, deleting pages, dividing and combining content, improving key word consistency etc.
: She/He usually works in the source code.


