===Chances===
How can you address the different user roles in the wiki?

; Reader
: Put the search bar upfront
: Show what can be found in this wiki
: Show clearly how you can find your way through this wiki
: Offer more than one possibility to reach content (main page, navigation, search bar, dashboards and overview sections, text links, breadcrumbs, direct URL input)
: Make the search fast, show relevant results, give search feedback, let filter results, make clear how search was interpreted.
: Overview sections: dashboards (automatized, after user role and department, and individualized): New in the wiki, latest changes (page, user), authors of pages
: Usability in GUI: Mouseover on buttons/links, clear error feedback

; Contributor
: Make working in the wiki seamless and easy, reduce clutter, engage participation
: Show clearly where to find help, and ways how to learn the details.
: Make it easy to report back improvement ideas.
: Make editing a pleasurable experience

; Power user/peer
: Give tools for easy improvement of the wiki: formatting, structuring
: Do not slow down engagement, but give possibility to shine
: Reward engagement
: Show authors/contributions on pages
: Help learning process for wiki functionalities
: Give peer position, facilitate communication with other users
: Encourage promotion
: Ease source editing (wiki editor)
: Make it easy to find out what pages would need creation
: Make it easy to ask for functionality ideas, improvement wishes, make list managable

; Gardener
: Give tools for monitoring the wiki easily (special pages, extra dashboard)
:: Give tools for easy categorization (if needed), give tools for easy marking of pages
: Develop tools and guidelines for editing in the wiki, involve gardener heavily in the process
: Key word management
: Make gardening work ending, not never-ending (Sisyphus)
: Give rights to claim help from others
: Give rewards and visibility for the work


